.TH TUNECRAFT 1 "2026" "TuneCraft 3.1.3" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tunecraft \- offline music player with DSP processing and local play-history journaling
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tunecraft
[\fIFILE\fR]
[\fB\-\-headless\fR]
[\fB\-\-analyze\fR]
[\fB\-\-skip-scan\fR]
[\fB\-\-skip-analysis\fR]
[\fB\-\-help\fR]
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tunecraft
is a high-fidelity, offline music player featuring a parametric equalizer,
loudness normalisation, BPM detection, real-time spectrum analysis, synced
lyrics via LRCLIB, and local play-history journaling.  It uses an egui/eframe
graphical interface with a wgpu back-end and supports the MPRIS D-Bus protocol
on Linux.
.PP
Supported audio formats: MP3, FLAC, OGG/Vorbis, WAV, AAC.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I FILE
Open and play a specific audio file on launch.
.TP
.B \-\-headless, \-\-cli
Run without the graphical interface (library management only).
.TP
.B \-\-analyze
Force loudness/BPM analysis on every track missing either, including
pre-v3.0.0 libraries where the loudness columns existed but were never
populated.  Implies \fB\-\-headless\fR.
.TP
.B \-\-skip-scan
Skip the startup library scan (headless mode only).
.TP
.B \-\-skip-analysis
Skip the startup audio-analysis pass (headless mode only).
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print a short usage summary and exit.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B RUST_LOG
Log level filter (e.g.\& \fBinfo\fR, \fBdebug\fR, \fBwarn\fR).  Default: \fBinfo\fR.
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Override the directory used for the SQLite library database and play-history
journal.  Defaults to \fI~/.local/share/tunecraft\fR.
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Override the directory used for \fIconfig.toml\fR.
Defaults to \fI~/.config/tunecraft\fR.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/tunecraft/config.toml
TOML configuration file.  Created with defaults on first run.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/tunecraft/library.db
SQLite database storing the music library, play counts, and cached lyrics.
.SH PLATFORM NOTES
Media key integration (play, pause, next, previous) is available on all
platforms via the \fBsouvlaki\fR library:
\fBLinux\fR uses the MPRIS D-Bus protocol, \fBmacOS\fR uses
MPRemoteCommandCenter, and \fBWindows\fR uses SystemMediaTransportControls.
Advanced MPRIS controls (Seek, SetPosition, OpenUri, shuffle, loop, etc.)
are available on \fBLinux only\fR.
